Uses of Package
guardians.model.entities

  • Packages that use guardians.model.entities 
    Package Description
    guardians.controllers
    Contains the controllers responsible for handling all requests of this application
    guardians.controllers.exceptions
    Contains the exceptions that will be thrown when handling a request
    guardians.model.assembler
    Contains the classes responsible of the creation of links in the resources
    guardians.model.entities
    Contains the Jpa Entities that will represent the different resources used in the application
    guardians.model.repositories
    Contains the repository interfaces used to access the data-source configured.
    guardians.model.validation
    Contains the custom annotations and classes created to validate entities
  • Classes in guardians.model.entities used by guardians.controllers 
    Class and Description
    AllowedShift
    AllowedShift represents the shifts a Doctor may have in their unwanted/unavailable/wanted/mandatory shifts
    Calendar
    The Calendar Entity represents a certain month o a certain year, and might have some specific configuration besides the specified in ShiftConfiguration and ShiftCycle.
    Doctor
    This Entity represents the information of a Doctor that will be stored in the database
    Schedule
    The Schedule Entity represents the scheduled shifts of a specific Calendar Note the primary key of this entity is composite, hence the IdClass annotation.
    ShiftConfiguration
    The ShiftConfiguration entities represent the configuration that will be applied whenever a shifts are scheduled.
  • Classes in guardians.model.entities used by guardians.controllers.exceptions 
    Class and Description
    Absence
    This Entity represents the Absence of a Doctor during a certain period An absence may occur, for example, if the Doctor is sick or in their holidays Absence is a weak entity.
